  "text": "A CBR value increases with the addition of course material due to the increase of frictional resistance and incompressibility of the additive material as well as leading to the enhanced bearing capacity of the mixed material [CITATION_1] . Tested CBR results are shown in Table 4 . The results from CBR-A revealed that the mixing of CC from 25% to 70% increased the CBR value from 1.21 to 2.39 times and became more effective than the mixing of IA. The results from CBR-D revealed that addition of CC with DWS from 25% to 70% enhanced CBR values from 1.44 to 2.97 times as compared to individual materials. This could be due to an increase of interlocking, well packing of fine and coarse proportions. On the other hand, IA blended with DWS did not show any improvement at higher compaction energy. The addition of both CC and IA to DWS increased CBR values, but the increase would be attributed to the inclusion of CC.",
